# BackgroundCircles Integration Examples

This document shows how to integrate the `BackgroundCircles` component into your application.

## Example 1: Basic Integration with Existing App

To add the animated background to your existing grid-based app:

```tsx
import { createRoot } from "react-dom/client";
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { motion, AnimatePresence } from "framer-motion";
import "./styles.css";
import { BackgroundCircles } from "./components/BackgroundCircles"; // Add this import
import { ManifestoPage } from "./pages/ManifestoPage";
import { WaitlistPage } from "./pages/WaitlistPage";

function App() {
  const [currentRoute, setCurrentRoute] = useState<Route>("manifesto");
  const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = useState(false);
  // ... rest of your state

  return (
    <>
      {/* Add BackgroundCircles as the first element */}
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <div className="grid-wrapper">
        <div className="grid-container">
          {/* Your existing grid cells */}
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}
```

## Example 2: Standalone Page

Create a standalone page with just the animated background:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function LandingPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{
      position: "relative",
      minHeight: "100vh",
      display: "flex",
      alignItems: "center",
      justifyContent: "center"
    }}>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        textAlign: "center",
        padding: "2rem"
      }}>
        <h1>Welcome to My App</h1>
        <p>Beautiful animated backgrounds made simple</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Example 3: Multiple Sections

Use the background across multiple sections:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function MultiSectionPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <section style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        minHeight: "100vh",
        padding: "4rem 2rem"
      }}>
        <h1>Section 1</h1>
        <p>Content goes here</p>
      </section>

      <section style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        minHeight: "100vh",
        padding: "4rem 2rem"
      }}>
        <h1>Section 2</h1>
        <p>More content here</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Example 4: With Dark Mode Support

Adjust opacity based on dark mode:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

export function DarkModeApp() {
  const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", darkMode);
  }, [darkMode]);

  return (
    <div>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        minHeight: "100vh",
        padding: "2rem",
        // Adjust content opacity for better visibility
        backgroundColor: darkMode
          ? "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3)"
          : "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3)"
      }}>
        <button onClick={() => setDarkMode(!darkMode)}>
          Toggle Dark Mode
        </button>
        <h1>Content</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Example 5: Hero Section with Overlay

Create a hero section with semi-transparent overlay:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function HeroSection() {
  return (
    <div style={{ position: "relative", minHeight: "100vh" }}>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      {/* Semi-transparent overlay for better text readability */}
      <div style={{
        position: "absolute",
        top: 0,
        left: 0,
        right: 0,
        bottom: 0,
        backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)",
        backdropFilter: "blur(2px)",
        zIndex: 0
      }} />

      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        height: "100vh",
        display: "flex",
        flexDirection: "column",
        alignItems: "center",
        justifyContent: "center",
        padding: "2rem"
      }}>
        <h1 style={{ fontSize: "3rem", marginBottom: "1rem" }}>
          Amazing Product
        </h1>
        <p style={{ fontSize: "1.5rem", marginBottom: "2rem" }}>
          With beautiful animated backgrounds
        </p>
        <button style={{
          padding: "1rem 2rem",
          fontSize: "1.125rem",
          backgroundColor: "#007bff",
          color: "white",
          border: "none",
          borderRadius: "0.5rem",
          cursor: "pointer"
        }}>
          Get Started
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Example 6: Side-by-Side Layout

Use in a split-screen layout:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function SplitLayout() {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", minHeight: "100vh" }}>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      {/* Left panel */}
      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        flex: 1,
        padding: "2rem",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)"
      }}>
        <h2>Left Content</h2>
        <p>This side has a white background</p>
      </div>

      {/* Right panel */}
      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        flex: 1,
        padding: "2rem",
        backgroundColor: "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8)",
        color: "white"
      }}>
        <h2>Right Content</h2>
        <p>This side has a dark background</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Example 7: Card Grid Layout

Use as background for a card grid:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function CardGrid() {
  const cards = [
    { id: 1, title: "Card 1", content: "Description 1" },
    { id: 2, title: "Card 2", content: "Description 2" },
    { id: 3, title: "Card 3", content: "Description 3" },
    { id: 4, title: "Card 4", content: "Description 4" },
  ];

  return (
    <div style={{ position: "relative", minHeight: "100vh", padding: "2rem" }}>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        display: "grid",
        gridTemplateColumns: "repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr))",
        gap: "2rem",
        maxWidth: "1200px",
        margin: "0 auto"
      }}>
        {cards.map(card => (
          <div key={card.id} style={{
            padding: "2rem",
            backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)",
            borderRadius: "0.5rem",
            boxShadow: "0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)"
          }}>
            <h3>{card.title}</h3>
            <p>{card.content}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Important Notes

### Z-Index Management

The `BackgroundCircles` component uses `z-index: -1` to stay behind your content. Make sure your content has:

```css
position: relative;
z-index: 1; /* or higher */
```

### Performance Tips

1. **Mobile Devices**: The component automatically reduces circle count on mobile
2. **Reduced Motion**: Respects `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
3. **Multiple Instances**: Avoid rendering multiple instances of the component

### Styling Considerations

The component works best when your content has:
- Semi-transparent backgrounds for visibility
- Sufficient contrast for readability
- Proper z-index stacking

### CSS Module Usage (Optional)

If you want to use the CSS module for additional styling:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";
import styles from "../components/BackgroundCircles.module.css";

export function StyledPage() {
  return (
    <div className={styles.backgroundCircles}>
      <BackgroundCircles />
      {/* Your content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Pattern 1: Full-Page Background
```tsx
<BackgroundCircles />
```
Place at the root level for app-wide background.

### Pattern 2: Section Background
Wrap content sections with proper z-index management.

### Pattern 3: Overlay Enhancement
Add semi-transparent overlays for better readability.

## Troubleshooting

### Content Not Visible
Ensure your content has `position: relative` and `z-index: 1` or higher.

### Performance Issues
The component automatically optimizes for different screen sizes. If issues persist, check browser DevTools Performance tab.

### Circles Not Animating
Verify that `requestAnimationFrame` is supported in your environment.

