## Example 7: Card Grid Layout

Use as background for a card grid:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";

export function CardGrid() {
  const cards = [
    { id: 1, title: "Card 1", content: "Description 1" },
    { id: 2, title: "Card 2", content: "Description 2" },
    { id: 3, title: "Card 3", content: "Description 3" },
    { id: 4, title: "Card 4", content: "Description 4" },
  ];

  return (
    <div style={{ position: "relative", minHeight: "100vh", padding: "2rem" }}>
      <BackgroundCircles />

      <div style={{
        position: "relative",
        zIndex: 1,
        display: "grid",
        gridTemplateColumns: "repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr))",
        gap: "2rem",
        maxWidth: "1200px",
        margin: "0 auto"
      }}>
        {cards.map(card => (
          <div key={card.id} style={{
            padding: "2rem",
            backgroundColor: "rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)",
            borderRadius: "0.5rem",
            boxShadow: "0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)"
          }}>
            <h3>{card.title}</h3>
            <p>{card.content}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Important Notes

### Z-Index Management

The `BackgroundCircles` component uses `z-index: -1` to stay behind your content. Make sure your content has:

```css
position: relative;
z-index: 1; /* or higher */
```

### Performance Tips

1. **Mobile Devices**: The component automatically reduces circle count on mobile
2. **Reduced Motion**: Respects `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
3. **Multiple Instances**: Avoid rendering multiple instances of the component

### Styling Considerations

The component works best when your content has:
- Semi-transparent backgrounds for visibility
- Sufficient contrast for readability
- Proper z-index stacking

### CSS Module Usage (Optional)

If you want to use the CSS module for additional styling:

```tsx
import { BackgroundCircles } from "../components/BackgroundCircles";
import styles from "../components/BackgroundCircles.module.css";

export function StyledPage() {
  return (
    <div className={styles.backgroundCircles}>
      <BackgroundCircles />
      {/* Your content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Pattern 1: Full-Page Background
```tsx
<BackgroundCircles />
```
Place at the root level for app-wide background.

### Pattern 2: Section Background
Wrap content sections with proper z-index management.

### Pattern 3: Overlay Enhancement
Add semi-transparent overlays for better readability.

## Troubleshooting

### Content Not Visible
Ensure your content has `position: relative` and `z-index: 1` or higher.

### Performance Issues
The component automatically optimizes for different screen sizes. If issues persist, check browser DevTools Performance tab.

### Circles Not Animating
Verify that `requestAnimationFrame` is supported in your environment.

